[00:10.80]If my name ever crosses your mind one day,
[00:13.87]If you hear my voice when you kneel and pray,
[00:16.93]Don’t lift me up, don’t sing my praise,
[00:20.00]I’m just a sinner saved by mercy and grace.
[00:23.06]I’ve seen this world turn bitter and mean,
[00:26.12]Hearts grow hard where love should be,
[00:29.19]And it cuts me deep, the pain I see,
[00:32.25]Lord knows this life can be heavy on me.
[00:35.32]Mm-hmm… mercy, Lord
[00:38.39]Yes, grace…
[00:41.45]If my life ever says a word at all—
[00:44.52]Let it tell ‘em ‘bout the Lord
[00:47.58]If my feet ever walks a narrow road—
[00:50.64]Point ‘em to the cross
[00:53.71]Don’t remember me—
[00:56.78]Remember the cross
[00:59.84]The blood that was shed—
[01:02.91]For the sinner lost
[01:05.97]If my voice moves your heart to believe—
[01:09.03]Fall on your knees
[01:12.10]At the foot of that old rugged tree
[01:15.16]I’m just a sign on a dusty road—
[01:18.23]Pointin’ home
[01:21.30]To a Savior who carried the load—
[01:24.36]Jesus bore it all
[01:27.42]If you see anything good in me—
[01:30.49]Give Him the glory
[01:33.55]Let it lead you straight to Jesus, not me
[01:36.62]I love every soul, the broken, the weak,
[01:39.69]The ones who still think they’re too far gone to reach,
[01:42.75]I’ve sat with the hurt, I’ve heard their cries,
[01:45.81]Seen hope come alive through tear-filled eyes.
[01:48.88]This world’s got a way of tearing you down,
[01:51.94]Chewing up faith, grinding saints in the ground,
[01:55.01]But there’s a hope that never runs dry—
[01:58.07]It stood in a grave… and walked out alive.
[02:01.14]He got up!
[02:04.20]Yes He did!
[02:07.27]I ain’t the truth, I ain’t the way—
[02:10.34]Jesus Is!
[02:13.40]I’m just a voice trying to say—
[02:16.47]He saves!
[02:19.53]Don’t remember me—
[02:22.59]Remember the cross
[02:25.66]The nails, the thorns—
[02:28.73]The sacri-fice
[02:31.79]If my song ever reaches your soul—
[02:34.86]Let Him take control
[02:37.92]Fall down at Calvary
[02:40.99]I’m just a witness, I can't save—
[02:44.05]Give it! to a risen King and an empty grave—
[02:47.12]The grave couldn’t hold Him!
[02:50.18]If you hear anything when I speak—
[02:53.25]Hear Jesus!
[02:56.31]Let it sound like Jesus calling you, not me
[02:59.38]I didn’t save you
[03:02.44]He Does!
[03:05.50]I didn’t bleed
[03:08.57]He Did!
[03:11.64]I didn’t rise on the third day
[03:14.70]Jesus did!
[03:17.77]I didn’t break those chains you wear
[03:20.83]He broke ‘em!
[03:23.90]I just know the One who meets you there
[03:26.96]Thank You, Lord!
[03:30.03]So don’t remember me—
[03:33.09]Remember His name!
[03:36.16]The One who took our guilt and shame—
[03:39.22]Jesus!
[03:42.28]If my life ever leaves a trace—
[03:45.35]Let it point to grace!
[03:48.42]And mercy flowing from that place
[03:51.48]When my days are done and my voice is still—
[03:54.55]He’s still God!
[03:57.61]Let the echo stand on that lonely hill—
[04:00.68]Calvary!
[04:03.74]Remember Jesus…
[04:06.81]Don’t remember me
[04:09.87]Remember the cross…
[04:12.94]Remember His name…
[04:16.00]Jesus… Jesus…
